channel.description: I just tried Proxy Way, and it's too confusing. I added a proxy, started a service with that proxy, and proxying is set to on. But WhatIsMyIP still shows my regular IP. item.title: Proxy Programs
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

SETO:

hey is there a way to open internet explor or mortilla using proxy like make a bat file then enter ip and run it just like we did at aryan

No, but in those you can set proxy settings.

In IE; Tools–>Internet Options–>Connections tab–>Lan settings–>Check button to use a proxy–>Enter proxy–>Enter the port

In mozilla, Tools–>Options–>General Tab–>Connecton settings–>Enter IP–>Enter port

etc…
